subSubSection.paragraph:
The upper tooth row is long and complete at both sides, including P2-4, M1-3. All the teeth are moderately worn and the enamel morphology is visible (
Fig. 2D
). The protocone is elliptical and flattened lingually, especially in the molars. The enamel plication is rich (mean plication is 20) with deep plis. The hypocone is elliptical with relatively deep distal hypoconal grooves. The plicabaline is strong, short and single or long and double/multiple.

